Cicero's daughter Tullia met him at Brundisium, but his wife did not (Manu- tius, quoted by Halm). Manutius refers to Plutarch (Cicero, c. 41), but in that pas- sage Plutarch is speaking of Cicero's return to Brundisium in 13.e. 48. In Β. e. 49 be had crossed the gulf to Pompeius in Epirus, and he returned to Italy through Brundisium after the battle of Pharsalia.
